badswalu wrote:
&gt; Sorry for the complication.
&gt; What I mean by a document is a file.
&gt; 
&gt; But to be more specific I want to use a different writer if we have
&gt; found malware or something we think is malware.
&gt; 
&gt; Therefore it should look more like this:
&gt; 
&gt; public DeciderWriter {
&gt;  
&gt; if we found malware
&gt;    writer1.innerProcess();
&gt; 
&gt; else 
&gt;    writer2.innerProcess();
&gt;  
&gt; }

You could do this by including both Writers in the processing chain, but 
then have each be disabled, via its per-processor DecideRules (in 
1.12+), for the URIs it should not write.

For example, you might have your own MalwareDetectorProcessor early in 
the chain, which marks up the CrawlURI (in its Alist) to indicate its 
malware status.

Then, implement DecideRules which answer REJECT when this status is set, 
or not set. (You could do this with your own DecideRule subclass, or 
leverage the BeanshellDecideRule to run a small script testing for the 
malware AList attribute.)

- Gordon @ IA

